cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper deals with automatic analysis of facial behavior of patients with schizophrenia, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The proposed SchiNet architecture is a neural network, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG) techniques. The use of videos for analysis also involves multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
